@@TJvMaxPixel.Font
Description:
This property is the font used to compute the width of text. If the UseControlFont is true, this property is ignored and the font of the control is used instead. This property is quite usefull if you want to limit the width of the text for a specific device (a printer) who uses another font than the system one.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvMaxPixel.Length
Description:
Use this property to limit the width of the text. The limited width is in pixel, and the font used to control the width is either the font of the control or another font. If you want to use another font, set the UseControlFont property to false and mofidy the font property. 

If this property is 0, there is no limitation of the text.

